\f1\b \cf2 Intro: \'a0
\f0\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Review of the past few weeks about hiding and how we all do it\'85that there are fears that move us to do odd things in life.\uc0\u8232 \
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Last week we discovered that when we fear losing control we step out of Role in life and into others\'85causing chaos for us and those around us\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf3 \strokec3 Transition: \'a0This week we continue the story of this man named Saul and we are going to see a common fear that plagues us all but is SO subtle that if we\'92re not careful it will invade all places in our lives...
\f0\b0 \cf2 \strokec2 \
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 Samuel said to Saul, \'93I am the one the Lord sent to anoint you king over his people Israel; so listen now to the message from the Lord. 
\f1\b 2 
\f0\b0 This is what the Lord\'a0Almighty says: \'91I will punish the Amalekites for what they did to Israel when they waylaid them as they came up from Egypt. 
\f1\b 3 
\f0\b0 Now go, attack the Amalekites and totally destroy\'a0all that belongs to them. Do not spare them; put to death men and women, children and infants, cattle and sheep, camels and donkeys.\'92\'94\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 This is a hard one to confuse\'85literally everything. \'a0Destroy it all. \'a0Nothing survives, nothing is exempt. \'a0\uc0\u8232 \
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 This couldn\'92t be easier to evaluate whether you\'92ve done it right or not\'85one question\'85is anything still left alive? \'a0Yes\'85kill it\'85No\'85we\'92re good!\uc0\u8232 \
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 It really is that simple\uc0\u8232 \
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 And yet sometimes what we will see is that it is the simple things that mess us up.\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf4 \strokec4 7 
\f0\b0 Then Saul attacked the Amalekites all the way from Havilah to Shur, near the eastern border of Egypt. 
\f1\b 8 
\f0\b0 He took Agag king of the Amalekites alive, and all his people he totally destroyed with the sword.\'a0\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Alive\'85not dead\'85but alive. \'a0This is problematic.\uc0\u8232 \
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 There is this disconnect that we are going to start to see here that is repeated\uc0\u8232 \
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 God said kill everything\'85and in the passage it says he destroyed everything\'85and kept Agag alive. \'a0\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \strokec5 Illustration of me telling someone they can have anything they want but every time they ask for something I say not that\'85and then tell them they can have anything though\'85there is a disconnect. \'a0I said\'a0everything, I didn\'92t say that!\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 What I want you to see is there is a good chance you have a disconnect too. \'a0\uc0\u8232 \
\ls4\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 (Sit here for a second)\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf4 \strokec4 9 
\f0\b0 But Saul and the army spared Agag and the best of the sheep and cattle, the fat calves\'a0and lambs\'97everything that was good. These they were 
\f1\b unwilling
\f0\b0  to destroy completely, but everything that was despised and weak they totally destroyed.\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 So if it is bad they killed it but if it was valuable then let\'92s not.\uc0\u8232 \
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 And in this moment it should have been clear whether Saul was obeying God or not but as we are going to see\'85sometimes what should be clear can get changed.\uc0\u8232 \
